description._content: Catalog #: 15_001723 Title: 1929 Schneider Race at Calshot, England ADDITIONAL INFORMATION: Entrants in the 1929 Schneider Trophy race were photographed during the mooring-out portion of the race's prerequisites. From left to right are Monti's Macchi M.67 (no. 10), Waghorn's Supermarine S.6 (no. 2), Dal Molin's Macchi M.52R (no. 4), D'Arcy Greig's Supermarine S.5 (no. 5), and Cadringher's M.67 (no. 7). Behind them is the launch used by the R.A.F. as a floating command station. Album Name: La Coppa Schneider 1982 Collection: Charles M. Daniels Collection Photo Page #: 44 Tags: 1929 Schneider Race at Calshot, England PUBLIC COMMONS.SOURCE INSTITUTION: San Diego Air and Space Museum Archive
